Bar Deco has 3 floors with indoor seating on the 2nd floor and rooftop on the 3rd, it has great happy hour deals with $8 cocktails and a few dollars off apps from 3-7pm  Truffle Fries with Bacon (5/5) - The crispy curled potato wedges hit the spot! They come with bacon, easy to request without.  Roasted Veggie Taco (5/5) - Compact and overflowing with sweet potatoes, greens, black bean puree, caramelized onion, scallions, and topped with spicy red pepper sauce and cheese. Bursting with flavor in every bite!  Margherita Flatbread (3/5) - Bland and boring. I was the flatbread was grilled and there was fresh slices of mozzarella cheese and pesto.  $8 Cocktails (4/5) - Of the 3 cocktails, I've ordered here - the G&T Rose was my favorite. The Vodka Collins is too sugary sweet, while the Rose Spritz feel flat. Wish it was more bubbly! Don't expect craft cocktails, you're paying for the outdoor space. Booked an online res for a party of 10, 4 days before the intended celebration. Bar Deco was chosen because of largely good reviews, food choices and convenient location for people coming to celebrate my birthday from MD and VA (one person coming was 9.5 mos pregnant). I even called after the online res was made to confirm it was received, and ask that a high chair be included for a 2 yr old in the party. Asked if that was ok. Told yes. I explained it was for a birthday, and told that would be noted. I was told no problem several times.  Roughly 90 minutes prior to the reservation, I was TEXTED yes, TEXTED, and told “we can’t accomodate your whole party at a table but can seat you in the bar, ok?” Ummm, no. Couldn’t believe what I was reading. Texted back. No reply. Waited 15 minutes....Stopped what I was doing, found a quiet place to make a call, expressed my frustration, was told, “ yeah on Sundays we don’t open our dining area, so we can put you in the bar...” Huh?! Explained res was made days ago, follow up call made that same day, and confirmed it was no problem...now I had people coming for MD and VA, and no effort was made to accomodate us, no apology, no nothing.  I explained I’d be writing an unfavorable review and letting everyone I knew not to choose this place for any sort of special occasion, especially with a large party. Luckily, found another restaurant happy to accomodate us, and caught all the guests in time.  So no, Bar Deco. Not ok. Not even close.

Was very much looking to enjoy the atmosphere and the food, however a little over an hour before our reservation for 10, the restaurant TEXTED to cancel our reservation. Res was made online and a follow up call was made to verify accommodation and a high chair. At the time of call it was all confirmed, no problem. Fast forward 4 days and now when calling to confirm cancellation text, the employee was stating the dining area isn’t open on Sundays and only the bar was. This is really poor customer service. Scratching them off the list due to poor customer service before we even entered the door.

Arrived at 545pm on a Monday night. Caps game at 7pm so it was very busy but several tables were still open.  Nice hostess who walked us up to the second floor bar/dining room.  Short wait and cordial waitress took order for happy hour beers, appetizer, and two burgers (it was half price burger night).  It was clear from adjacent tables that they were a bit short staffed and that the kitchen was a bit backed up.  Beers came out in about 10 min and app in about 25 min. Burgers never came out....ever.  After 50 min or so and other tables getting their food (paying bill and leaving) we asked for a manager. The two different waiter/waitress we had were checking on us every 5-10 min or so and continually apologized for the delay but I don't think anyone ever checked with the kitchen or computer to make sure our burgers had been ordered.  Manager was very apologetic and comped the full meal and another round of beers.  However, if we wanted our food within 20 minutes (this 70 min after ordering for 90+ min total)  the only options were nachos, wings, or tacos. We being hungry and having a pressing engagement (thankfully not the Caps game as we would have been very late) requested nachos so we could get at least some sustenance. I have no idea why our burgers couldn't be rushed but the manager candidly said our only options at that point were the 2 apps or tacos.  In the end:  Pros: they made it right by comping the meal, everyone was apologetic, the two apps we had were relatively tasty, service was as good as could be expected given the amount of wait staff vs crowd.  Cons: It should never take over over 90 min to get two burgers on burger night even if there is an error entering them or whatever happened....we never even got them and despite our wait they couldn't make 2 medium burgers in 20 min even though the hockey crowd was gone and we were literally the only people left..!!??? Also it's really dark in the dining room (not a huge deal but more lighting would be ideal). We would likely not go back any time soon but we did appreciate the willingness to comp the bill and that the staff was nice.

I went here for brunch with my cousin back in February. A couple days after, my cousins credit card was hacked and all these charges were placed on it. We assumed it was from this place since this was the only place she used it recently. Fast forward to the second week in July I took a friend here (because Free State around the corner wasn’t open yet) for a quick beer on the rooftop (which is very nice). I check my credit card and see that my card was hacked as well.
